<subSubSection pageId="137" pageNumber="534" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="137.[171,1378,290,559]" pageId="137" pageNumber="534">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[173,518,365,398]" pageId="137" pageNumber="534">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The [UCN Red List. The Somali White-toothed Shrew has a very wide distribution, butit is only known from a few scattered records and is considered rare throughout its known distribution.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
